#Text=Anna Koldings
#Text=Anna ( Ane or Anne ) Koldings ( died 1590 ) was an alleged Danish witch .
#Text=She was one of the main suspects in the witch trial of Copenhagen the summer of 1590 , which were held as a parallel to the famous North Berwick Witch trials in Edinburgh in Scotland .
#Text=The winter of 1589 , Princess Anne of Denmark departed from Copenhagen to marry King James VI of Scotland .
#Text=A great storm arose , which almost caused the ship to sink .

#Text=The ship of the princess eventually harbored in Oslo in the Danish province of Norway , James VI joined her there , and the wedding took place in Norway instead of in Scotland , as had been planned .
#Text=In the spring of 1590 , James VI returned to Scotland after his marriage .
#Text=The regal voyage back from Denmark was beset by storms .
#Text=The Danish court at that time was greatly perplexed by witchcraft and the black arts , and this must have impressed on the young King James . [ 1 ]
#Text=In the summer of 1590 , a great witch hunt was instituted in Copenhagen .
#Text=The Danish authorities issued an investigation to the cause of the storms .

#Text=The Danish minister of finance , Christoffer Valkendorff , was accused by the Admiral Peder Munk of having equipped the royal ship so insufficiently that it had been unable to withstand storm . [ 2 ]

#Text=He defended himself by saying that the storm had been caused by witches in the house of Karen the Weaver , who had sent little demons in empty barrows who had climbed up the keels of the ships and caused the storm . [ 3 ]
#Text=Karen was arrested in July .
#Text=She confessed to have caused the storms which hunted the royal ship by use of witchcraft , and named other women as accomplices .
#Text=One of them was Anna Koldings .

#Text=During torture , Koldings described how a group of women had gathered in the house of Karen , where they had caused the storm of the princess ' ship by sending small devils up the keels of the ship .
#Text=She named five other women as accomplices , among them Malin , wife of the mayor of Copenhagen , and Margrethe Jakob Skrivers .
#Text=All women were arrested and charged , while the spouse of Skrivers unsuccessfully tried to defend her .
#Text=Anne Koldings was considered a very dangerous witch , and referred to as Mother of the Devil .
#Text=She was treated as somewhat of a celebrity in prison and displayed to visitors :
#Text=she is known to have confessed to two priests and three female visitors while in prison .
#Text=Anne Koldings was judged guilty as charged and executed by burning at the stake at Kronborg .
#Text=Twelve women were reportedly executed for involvement in this witch trial .
#Text=In September , two women were burnt as witches at Kronborg . [ 4 ]
#Text=James heard news from Denmark regarding this , and decided to set up his own tribunal .
